SUMMARY:Hands on Impact: Greater Boston Food Bank 
DESCRIPTION:Category: ‘Quin Impact Fund\nPrice: Free\nStatus: Waitlist On
 ly\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175767\n\nJoin The 
 ’Quin Impact Fund for a hands-on volunteer experience at the Greater Bos
 ton Food Bank\, where members can make a tangible difference in the fight 
 against hunger across our community. Participants will help sort\, package
 \, and organize food donations that support thousands of neighbors in need
  throughout Greater Boston.\n\nThe Greater Boston Food Bank (GBFB)\, New E
 ngland’s largest hunger-relief organization and a member of Feeding Amer
 ica\, distributed 107 million pounds of nutritious food last year alone. T
 hrough the dedication of its staff\, volunteers\, and partners\, GBFB work
 s to provide three meals a day to every person in need in Eastern Massachu
 setts\, supporting healthy lives and thriving communities.\n\n*This event 
 is complimentary and reserved for members only. Please wear comfortable cl
 othing suitable for service and close-toed shoes.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175767
CATEGORIES:‘Quin Impact Fund
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-167855@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260319T051558Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260322T090000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260322T120000
SUMMARY:'Quin Impact Fund: Winter Walk
LOCATION:Meet in Scottie's
DESCRIPTION:Category: ‘Quin Impact Fund\nPrice: Free\nAvailability: 14 sp
 ots left\nStatus: Available\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/e
 vents/167855\n\nThe ’Quin Impact Fund invites members to take part in Wi
 nter Walk\, a powerful call to action to help end homelessness in our city
 . This annual two-mile walk offers an opportunity to gather in solidarity 
 and experience\, if only briefly\, the winter conditions faced by Boston�
 �s unhoused neighbors.\n\nMembers are encouraged to meet at The ’Quin fo
 r complimentary hot beverages and coordinated ’Quin Impact Fund hats bef
 ore walking together to Boston Common for the official program. The mornin
 g will include remarks and storytelling from individuals with lived experi
 ence and service providers before the walk begins.\n\nWinter Walk is roote
 d in the belief that ending homelessness starts with ending stigma. By wal
 king side by side\, housed and unhoused\, we amplify voices too often unhe
 ard\, elevate the work of frontline organizations\, and affirm that homele
 ssness is a solvable crisis when met with compassion\, awareness\, and col
 lective will.\n\n*This event is complimentary and reserved for members onl
 y. By registering for this event\, you are authorizing The 'Quin House to 
 release your contact information to Winter Walk. To read the full Release 
 of Liability and Waiver\, click here. Members do not need to register sepa
 rately through Winter Walk.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/167855
CATEGORIES:‘Quin Impact Fund
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-175769@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260319T051558Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260323T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260323T160000
SUMMARY:'Quin Chat: A Conversation with Malala Yousafzai
LOCATION:The Reading Room
DESCRIPTION:Category: ‘Quin Chat\nPrice: Free\nStatus: Waitlist Only\nEve
 nt URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175769\n\n2:00PM Reception
 \, 2:30PM Discussion\nA powerful voice for education\, equity\, and global
  change takes the stage for this special ’Quin Chat.\n\nActivist\, autho
 r\, and Nobel Peace Prize laureate Malala Yousafzai\, in conversation with
  ‘Quin Co-Founder Sandy Edgerley\, reflects on the experiences that have
  shaped her remarkable journey - from her early advocacy for girls’ educ
 ation in Pakistan to becoming the youngest-ever recipient of the Nobel Pea
 ce Prize to recently founding the Women's Sports investment firm\, Recess 
 Capital. Drawing from her latest book\, Finding My Way\, Malala will exp
 lore the evolving balance between global activism and everyday life\, shar
 ing candid insights on purpose\, perseverance\, and what it means to lead 
 with conviction.\n\nRooted in themes of community\, education\, sport\, an
 d growth\, this conversation offers a thoughtful look at the next chapter 
 of Malala’s work and the enduring pursuit of a more equitable world.\n\n
 *This event is complimentary and reserved for members only. Complimentary 
 light bites and refreshments will be served.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175769
CATEGORIES:‘Quin Chat
END:VEVENT
