BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-169177@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260319T051558Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T130000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T150000
SUMMARY: 90 Minutes of Innovation: Top Gun Meets a $2+ Billion Aviation Gam
 e-Changer 
LOCATION:The Pub
DESCRIPTION:Category: ‘Quin Chat\nPrice: Free\nAvailability: 2 spots left
 \nStatus: You are Confirmed\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/e
 vents/169177\n\n1:00PM Program\, 2:30PM Networking \nTwo frontiers. One s
 tage. Not to be missed. In this high-voltage edition of 90 Minutes of Inno
 vation\, flight becomes more than a metaphor — it becomes a stress test 
 for the future of AI\, defense\, climate innovation\, and human judgment i
 tself.\n\nJohn Werner — venture capitalist\, Forbes AI columnist\, and I
 nnovation Curator at The ’Quin House — convenes an extraordinary pairi
 ng you won’t see anywhere else. A real-world Top Gun who has flown 80 co
 mbat missions\, 290 test missions\, and logged more than 2\,000 hours acro
 ss 30 aircraft — including the F-35\, F-15\, and F-16 — operating alon
 gside AI in live\, high-stakes environments. And a leader helping build on
 e of the most highly capitalized electric aviation companies in the world.
 \n\nFirst: Kristen Costello\n\nBuilding the Next Aviation System\n\nKriste
 n Costello is a pilot and executive at Vermont-based Beta Technologies\, a
  New England aerospace company valued at more than $2 billion and backed b
 y over $1 billion from Fidelity\, Qatar Investment Authority\, Amazon’s 
 Climate Pledge Fund\, GE Aerospace\, and others.\n\nBeta isn’t pitching 
 a concept. It’s building a new aviation system. Founded by former Harvar
 d hockey player Kyle Clark — once told not to return to Vermont because 
 “there was nothing there” — Beta has grown into one of the most ambi
 tious aerospace companies on the planet. The company is developing all-ele
 ctric aircraft for cargo\, medical logistics\, and passenger travel while 
 simultaneously constructing a nationwide charging network. It has complete
 d cross-country flights\, secured major commercial and defense partnership
 s\, and is advancing through the FAA’s rigorous certification process.\n
 \nThe breakthrough isn’t just the airplane. It’s the systems thinking 
 — aircraft\, charging infrastructure\, certification\, pilot training\, 
 and operations built in parallel. Not incremental change\, but a redesign 
 of regional air mobility from propulsion to power grid. If it succeeds\, i
 t won’t just change how we fly. It will change where flying makes sense.
 \n\nThen: Tucker “Cinco” Hamilton\n\nWhere Humans and AI Share the Coc
 kpit\n\nThe evening shifts to contested airspace.\n\nRetired U.S. Air Forc
 e Colonel and experimental fighter test pilot Tucker “Cinco” Hamilton 
 — former Chief of AI Test and Operations for the U.S. Air Force and Spac
 e Force — led the integration of AI-enabled autonomy into combat aircraf
 t. He has operated at the edge\, where algorithms and humans share the coc
 kpit in real-time\, high-consequence environments.\n\nHamilton brings audi
 ences inside moments few will ever experience: ejecting from a failing air
 craft\, managing an engine fire at twice the speed of sound\, crash-landin
 g a jet while fighting to keep it upright\, and flying combat missions ove
 r Afghanistan. For Hamilton\, AI is not theoretical. It is airborne. He ha
 s confronted the defining questions of our era:\n\nWhen should a machine b
 e trusted?\n\nHow do you test systems that learn?\n\nWhat happens when AI 
 evolves faster than doctrine?\n\nWho is accountable when autonomy acts?\n\
 nThis program also marks the debut of his new book\, Unlocking the Last 20
 %\, on elite performance in an age of automation.\n\nAviation has always p
 reviewed the future. Now it is revealing the operating system of the next 
 century. The future is not humans replaced by machines. It is humans redes
 igned alongside them.\n\n*This event is complimentary and reserved for mem
 bers only. Light bites and refreshments will be served.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/169177
CATEGORIES:‘Quin Chat
END:VEVENT
