BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-175771@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260319T051558Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T183000
SUMMARY:'Quin Chat: Rethinking Women's Health
LOCATION:Scottie's
DESCRIPTION:Category: Health & Wellness\nPrice: Free\nStatus: Waitlist Only
 \nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175771\n\n5:00PM Rece
 ption\, 5:30PM Discussion \nAs we celebrate Women's History Month\, join 
 us for a conversation about Women's Health—covering the science\, strate
 gies\, and emerging thinking shaping modern wellness. Moderated by Jay Lut
 har MD\, Founder and Medical Director of Lutanen Health & Faculty at Harva
 rd Medical School\, the discussion brings together leading voices tackling
  the topics women are asking about most.\n\nPelvic Floor Physical Therapis
 t Melissa Hines\, founder of Wellest\, will explore the often-overlooked r
 ole of pelvic health and the power of proactive care. Pelvic Health Nurse 
 Practitioner Kathy Kates will break down the realities of perimenopause an
 d hormone replacement therapy (HRT) - demystifying symptoms\, treatments\,
  and the everyday shifts that can support better balance. Internist and ge
 riatrician Julia Loewenthal MD of Lutanen Health & Assistant Professor at 
 Harvard Medical School will examine the latest research on longevity and H
 RT\, separating myth from evidence while reframing the conversation around
  long-term vitality.\n\nBlending medical insight with practical perspectiv
 e\, this series opens the door to a more informed\, modern dialogue around
  women’s health - one grounded in science\, curiosity\, and the pursuit 
 of living well at every stage.\n\n*This event is complimentary and reserve
 d for members only. Complimentary light bites and refreshments will be ser
 ved.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175771
CATEGORIES:Health & Wellness
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-173833@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260319T051558Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260324T210000
SUMMARY:Author's Circle Book Club: "Canticle" with Janet Rich Edwards 
LOCATION:The Muse
DESCRIPTION:Category: The Arts\nPrice: Free\nAvailability: 2 spots left\nSt
 atus: Available\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/173833
 \n\nBookmark the date for a compelling conversation exploring Canticle\, t
 he luminous debut novel by Janet Rich Edwards set in thirteenth-century Br
 uges - a story of faith\, independence\, and love.\n\nAt sixteen\, Aleys i
 s serious\, stubborn\, and prone to religious visions. When her closest co
 mpanion abandons her for the monastery and her family promises her in marr
 iage to the calculating head of the weavers’ guild\, she refuses to acce
 pt the life chosen for her. Fleeing home\, she finds refuge among the Begu
 ines - an independent community of religious women who live and worship ou
 tside the authority of the Church.\n\nWithin this vibrant sisterhood\, Ale
 ys discovers scholarship\, friendship\, and a new sense of purpose. But as
  illicit translations of scripture circulate and reports of miracles sprea
 d\, the women’s autonomy draws dangerous scrutiny from Church authoritie
 s - forcing Aleys to confront the true cost of devotion\, love\, and sacri
 fice.\n\nJoin us for a thoughtful discussion of this richly imagined histo
 rical novel and its stirring portrait of spiritual awakening and female ag
 ency.\n\n*This event is complimentary and reserved for members only. Light
  bites and refreshments will be served.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/173833
CATEGORIES:The Arts
END:VEVENT
