BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-175778@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260319T051558Z
DTSTART;TZID=America/New_York:20260327T170000
DTEND;TZID=America/New_York:20260327T183000
SUMMARY:'Quin Chat: The Edge of Possible with Monet Izabeth 
LOCATION:Scottie's
DESCRIPTION:Category: ‘Quin Chat\nPrice: Free\nAvailability: 3 spots left
 \nStatus: Available\nEvent URL: https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/17
 5778\n\n5:00PM Reception\, 5:30PM Discussion \nAn evening of extraordinar
 y endurance and perspective awaits with solo adventurer and storyteller Mo
 net Izabeth. In January 2026\, she became the first American woman to ski 
 solo and unsupported to the South Pole\, traveling 700 miles across Antarc
 tica over 57 days. Alone in whiteouts and subzero temperatures\, hauling e
 very supply herself\, her expedition was a profound test of resilience\, p
 reparation\, and the decision to begin before feeling fully ready.\n\nBase
 d between Massachusetts and Nepal\, Monet has built her career designing i
 mmersive\, locally led journeys that connect travelers more deeply to plac
 e and people - while inspiring a global community to step beyond what feel
 s comfortable and into what feels possible.\n\nThe conversation will be mo
 derated by journalist Billy Baker\, who chronicled Monet’s journey\, off
 ering insight into both the public story\, the personal reality behind it 
 and what we can all learn from choosing the extraordinary. \n\n*This even
 t is complimentary and reserved for members only. Light bites and refreshm
 ents will be served.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/175778
CATEGORIES:‘Quin Chat
END:VEVENT
