BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:quin-event-166077@thequinhouse.com
DTSTAMP:20260319T051558Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260409
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260417
SUMMARY:'Venture: The Wonders of Egypt
LOCATION:Offsite: Cairo\, Egypt
DESCRIPTION:Category: ‘Venture - Travel\nPrice: $8528.04 per person\nStat
 us: Waitlist Only\nTime: 12 PM – 11 AM\nEvent URL: https://members.thequ
 inhouse.com/events/166077\n\nExperience Egypt Like Never Before. \nMore t
 han just a visit\, immerse yourself in the extraordinary world of ancient 
 Egypt with a trip designed to bring history\, culture\, and wonder vividly
  to life. From the moment you arrive in Cairo\, you’ll be guided seamles
 sly through a curated exploration of Egypt’s most iconic treasures—tow
 ering temples\, bustling bazaars\, storied deserts\, and the timeless wate
 rs of the Nile. Together with fellow ‘Quin members\, discover the depth 
 and richness of this remarkable civilization as you explore legendary site
 s including Karnak\, Luxor\, the Valley of the Kings\, Philae Temple\, and
  the awe-inspiring Pyramids of Giza. Throughout the trip\, your dedicated 
 tour coordinators and expert Egyptologists will offer unparalleled insight
  into the stories\, symbolism\, and craftsmanship that have shaped Egypt a
 cross millennia.\n\nYour journey begins at the luxurious Waldorf Astoria C
 airo\, a serene oasis from which to acclimate before continuing onward to 
 board the elegant A&K Sanctuary Nile Adventurer\, your private\, five-star
  floating home for the coming days. Thoughtfully designed and impeccably s
 erviced\, the vessel offers refined accommodations\, gourmet dining\, and 
 exceptional hospitality as you sail from Luxor to Aswan. Each day unveils 
 new discoveries—from cooking lessons and afternoon tea on deck to guided
  explorations of the temples of Edfu and Kom Ombo\, followed by a beautifu
 lly curated onboard celebration featuring regional cuisine\, music\, and w
 arm hospitality.\n\nAfter disembarking in Aswan\, your adventure continues
  back in Cairo with stays at the Four Seasons Nile Plaza\, where a series 
 of beautifully arranged experiences await\, from an evening walk through t
 he storied Khan El-Khalili Bazaar to a tranquil felucca sail along the ill
 uminated Nile and private guided visits to the Grand Egyptian Museum\, the
  Pyramids of Giza\, and Old Cairo’s architectural landmarks. This except
 ional journey offers a rare blend of history\, luxury\, and cultural immer
 sion—crafted to deliver an unforgettable exploration of Egypt’s past a
 nd present.\n\nDeluxe Cabin | Single Occupancy\nStandard Cabin Main Deck o
 n the Nile Adventure\n\nSuperior Room Citadel View King Bed at the Four Se
 asons Cairo\n\n$9\,125\n\nPremier Balcony | Double Occupancy\nStandard Cab
 in Promenade Deck on the Nile Adventure\n\nNile View Room with Balcony Ki
 ng Bed at the Four Seasons Cairo\n\n$13\,275\n\nDeluxe Balcony | Double O
 ccupancy\nStandard Cabin Bridge Deck on the Nile Adventure\n\nNile View Ro
 om with Balcony King Bed at the Four Seasons Cairo\n\n$13\,575\n\nReservat
 ions are available on a first-to-reserve basis and will remain open exclus
 ively to 'Quin members through January 31st. Members and their accompanyin
 g guests sharing member accommodations are most welcome.\n\nFor the smooth
 est arrival experience\, we recommend flying into Cairo International Airp
 ort (CAI)\, located just minutes from the Waldorf Astoria Cairo Heliopolis
 . To ensure your complimentary transfer\, please select flights arriving b
 etween 2:00 pm and 5:00 pm local time.\n\nGuests traveling from Boston wil
 l find convenient one-stop itineraries to Cairo with reputable internation
 al carriers such as Lufthansa\, Air France\, British Airways\, Turkish Air
 lines\, and EgyptAir. These routes offer reliable connections and comforta
 ble long-haul service.\n\nTransportation from the airport to the hotel wil
 l be provided for all members arriving within the recommended window. Shou
 ld you arrive outside this timeframe\, we are pleased to offer guidance fo
 r arranging independent transfers.\n\n*Space is limited and on a first to 
 reserve basis. Reservations are non-refundable and non-transferable. Plea
 se note that all bookings are subject to the terms and conditions outlined
  in the final confirmation materials.
URL:https://members.thequinhouse.com/events/166077
CATEGORIES:‘Venture - Travel
END:VEVENT
